  <div class="sublist_thumbs"><h4><a href="http://www.npr.org/books/">Books</a></h4><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/28/142659550/sherlockian-mysteries-that-will-keep-you-tied-up"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/28/mysteries_sq.jpg?t=1322491485&amp;s=11" alt="Maureen Corrigan selects the best new works of fiction and criticism about The Great Detective."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/28/142659550/sherlockian-mysteries-that-will-keep-you-tied-up">Sherlockian Mysteries That Will Keep You Tied Up</a></h3><p>Maureen Corrigan selects the best new works of fiction and criticism about The Great Detective.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/27/142664182/most-beautiful-woman-by-day-inventor-by-night"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/22/hedys_folly_sq.jpg?t=1322067082&amp;s=11" alt="Actress Hedy Lamarr invented a form of wireless communication that led to Bluetooth, GPS and more."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/27/142664182/most-beautiful-woman-by-day-inventor-by-night">'Most Beautiful Woman' By Day, Inventor By Night</a></h3><p>Actress Hedy Lamarr invented a form of wireless communication that led to Bluetooth, GPS and more.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/28/142310625/dusting-off-a-gritty-glamorous-california-classic"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/21/dustpromo_sq.jpg?t=1321892939&amp;s=11" alt="Author Hector Tobar recommends a novel that captures the grit and glamor of Los Angeles' past."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/28/142310625/dusting-off-a-gritty-glamorous-california-classic">Dusting Off A Gritty, Glamorous California Classic</a></h3><p>Author Hector Tobar recommends a novel that captures the grit and glamor of Los Angeles' past.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/25/142730724/bachmanns-conviction-to-fixing-government"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/24/507389321_9616033_sq.jpg?t=1322192716&amp;s=11" alt="In an interview with Steve Inskeep, the GOP candidate talks about her new memoir and aiming to win."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/25/142730724/bachmanns-conviction-to-fixing-government">Bachmann's 'Conviction' To Fixing Government</a></h3><p>In an interview with Steve Inskeep, the GOP candidate talks about her new memoir and aiming to win.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/26/142701523/unconquered-explores-an-isolated-amazon-tribe"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/23/91258952_sq.jpg?t=1322286790&amp;s=11" alt="Journalist Scott Wallace studies a group that hasn't come into contact with modern civilization."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/26/142701523/unconquered-explores-an-isolated-amazon-tribe">'Unconquered' Explores An Isolated Amazon Tribe</a></h3><p>Journalist Scott Wallace studies a group that hasn't come into contact with modern civilization.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/24/142729894/emily-dickinson-takes-over-tucson"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/23/emily-dickinson_sq.jpg?t=1322090566&amp;s=11" alt="The Big Read Project has inspired lectures, dances and even desserts in honor of the poet."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/24/142729894/emily-dickinson-takes-over-tucson">Emily Dickinson Takes Over Tucson</a></h3><p>The Big Read Project has inspired lectures, dances and even desserts in honor of the poet.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/26/142662771/chicks-with-guns-a-picture-of-gun-toting-women"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/23/alexandra-and-truitt-small_sq.jpg?t=1322332622&amp;s=11" alt="More than 15 million women in the U.S. are gun owners, and 78 of them are in a new photo book."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/26/142662771/chicks-with-guns-a-picture-of-gun-toting-women">'Chicks With Guns': A Picture Of Gun-Toting Women</a></h3><p>More than 15 million women in the U.S. are gun owners, and 78 of them are in a new photo book.</p></div></div><p class="more"><a href="http://www.npr.org/books/">more</a></p></div>

